/div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">This is my first attempt at marzipan and it has worked a treat! The quantity is sufficient to cover an 18cm square cake to a depth of nearly 1cm and the trimmings will taste fab dipped in melted dark chocolate, as suggested by another reviewer.
As I do when making pastry, I rolled my marzipan between clingfilm, which meant I needed no extra icing sugar and this made it easy to transfer to the cake (which I turned top down onto the marzipan then used the clingfilm to bring the marzipan up the sides before turning the right way up and trimming). Will definitely by making this again.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-719901"><a id="comment-719901"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">fionamckay</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 15th Dec, 2013</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">It looks like a large quantity, but in our house there's no such thing as too much marzipan, so that's good! Leftovers can always be dipped in dark chocolate to make petit fours....</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-719086"><a id="comment-719086"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">ruthwilliamson</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 11th Dec, 2013</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Great recipe and a good quantity for a top and sides of a square 20cm cake</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-114097"><a id="comment-114097"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"